sublevels.theory:
Every Java program needs a class and a `main` method:

```java
public class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello, World!");
    }
}
```

- `public class HelloWorld` — class name must match the filename
- `public static void main(String[] args)` — program entry point
- `System.out.println()` — prints with newline
- `System.out.print()` — prints without newline
- Every statement ends with `;`
- Java is **case-sensitive**
- Comments: `//` single-line, `/* */` multi-line, `/** */` Javadoc
